2072.subject: LL
2072.descrlong: Focuses on academic orientation in Liberal Learning and advanced writing, critical thinking, collaborative learning, and research skills. Introduces philosophies underlying the liberal arts, along with a multicultural historical view of social and political philosophy. Requires junior standing; successful completion of the English Communication (ENGCOM) and ETHICS University Learning Requirements (or their General Education equivalencies in written and oral communication and critical thinking). (LL Core class)
